现在让我们看看“语言要点”第二部分。

119
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,920
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

120
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:44,600
Okay, so the first word has to do with the eyes.
好的，第一个词和眼睛有关。

121
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,120
We just talked about the eyebrows.
我们刚刚讨论了眉毛。

122
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,320
Those are above your eyes.
它们在眼睛上方。

123
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:52,080
Well, what happens if your eyes are very, very deep in your face?
那么，如果你的眼睛在脸上非常深，会怎么样？

124
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:55,720
Okay, we heard that in the dialogue.
好的，我们在对话中听到了这个。

125
00:05:55,720 --> 00:06:00,160
We heard that in the dialogue described as sunken eyes.
我们在对话中听到它被描述为“凹陷的眼睛”。

126
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:05,960
So sunken means very far back or very deep in something.
所以“sunken”意思是某物非常靠后或非常深。

127
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:07,440
Think about a sunken ship.
想想一艘沉船。

128
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:10,180
It's under the water, under the ocean.
它在水下，在海洋下面。

129
00:06:10,180 --> 00:06:14,440
So someone with sunken eyes probably has dark rings under their eyes because their eyes
所以有凹陷眼睛的人可能眼睛下有黑眼圈，因为他们的眼睛

130
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:16,280
are so deep in their head.
在头部里很深。

131
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,280
That's right.
没错。

132
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:20,320
And the opposite, maybe you've seen people that have eyes that are almost like popping
相反的情况，也许你见过有些人眼睛几乎像要

133
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,320
out a little bit.
突出来一点。

134
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,320
Right.
对。

135
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:23,320
His eyes pop out.
他的眼睛突出来。

136
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,720
That means they come out of the face.
意思是它们从脸上凸出来。

137
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,640
They're closer to the skin.
它们更靠近皮肤。

138
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:27,640
That's right.
没错。

139
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:32,840
Okay, and now this is something that many people have and even some models have become
好的，现在这个是很多人有的，甚至有些模特因为

140
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,640
famous because of this.
这个而出名。

141
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:36,760
Many times called a beauty mark.
很多时候被称为美人痣。

142
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:38,360
We're talking about moles.
我们在说痣。

143
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:40,800
Cindy Crawford is probably the model you're talking about.
辛迪·克劳馥大概就是你说的那个模特。

144
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,360
She had a very famous mole.
她有一颗非常著名的痣。

145
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:48,560
A mole is basically a spot on your skin that's very, very dark.
痣基本上是你皮肤上一个非常非常黑的斑点。

146
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:51,480
So sometimes there's hair on it.
所以有时候上面有毛。

147
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,840
Sometimes its texture is different.
有时候它的质地不同。

148
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:54,960
But it can be big, it can be small.
但它可以大，也可以小。

149
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:58,960
But it's a change of texture on your skin.
但它是你皮肤上质地的变化。

150
00:06:58,960 --> 00:06:59,960
That's right.
没错。

151
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:04,280
So usually it's like a little brown ball if it's big.
所以通常如果它大，就像一个小棕色球。

152
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:08,720
And sometimes they just look like little spots on your skin, little dark brown spots.
有时候它们看起来就像皮肤上的小斑点，深棕色的小点。

153
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,720
That's right.
没错。

154
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,680
But they're not the same as something else we heard in today's dialogue.
但它们和我们今天对话中听到的另一个东西不一样。

155
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,680
So we'll wait for that.
所以我们等一下再说那个。

156
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:16,120
But a mole usually comes a little bit off the skin.
但痣通常稍微凸出皮肤一点。

157
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:18,780
And it's usually bigger than other dots.
而且通常比其他点大。

158
00:07:18,780 --> 00:07:19,780
That's right.
没错。

159
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:22,200
And I think what you're talking about is freckles.
我想你说的是雀斑。

160
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,200
That's right, freckles.
没错，雀斑。

161
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,640
A lot of people have these when they're children.
很多人小时候都有这个。

162
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:29,080
They come on your nose and your cheeks and even your arms.
它们会长在鼻子、脸颊，甚至胳膊上。

163
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:30,800
And they're smooth with your skin.
它们和皮肤一样平滑。

164
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,680
They don't come off your skin.
它们不会从皮肤上脱落。

165
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,900
They're not puffy.
它们不是鼓起来的。

166
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:35,900
That's right.
没错。

167
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:43,160
And I think many of you maybe if you have lighter skin may have freckles.
我想你们中很多人，如果皮肤比较白，可能就有雀斑。

168
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:48,120
And that's usually just little spots but of just different color on your skin.
那通常只是皮肤上颜色不同的小点。

169
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:53,240
So usually people that have maybe red hair, they have freckles.
所以通常红头发的人会有雀斑。

170
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:57,160
Like maybe from the Harry Potter movie, Harry Potter's best friend, I think Ron.
比如《哈利·波特》电影里，哈利·波特最好的朋友，我想是罗恩。

171
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,160
Ron, yeah.
罗恩，对。

172
00:07:58,160 --> 00:07:59,160
You can see he has freckles.
你可以看到他脸上有雀斑。

173
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:00,160
That's right.
没错。

174
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:02,600
On his skin he has lots of little dots.
他的皮肤上有很多小点。

175
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,640
Because he has very pale skin and red hair.
因为他皮肤很白，头发是红色的。

176
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:06,720
